          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1641914820256-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Mash the<strong> cooled potato</strong> until smooth</p><p>Add the <strong>gremolata fish</strong>,<strong> </strong>3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix until fully combined</p><p>Divide the mixture into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span>, then shape into fish cakes</p><p>Add the <strong>fish cakes </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and put the tray in the oven for 25 min, flipping once halfway for even cooking – these are your <strong>haddock & gremolata fish cakes</strong></p>",
